race.comment: Tricky. RUN PATTIE RUN (6) resumes and brings strong form from Bunbury and Pinjarra. She's won 2/3 fresh and has had a trial warmer at Lark Hill. Has an awkward gate, but Faithfull is a positive jockey booking, suggesting she's ready to go. HEZANGELIC (2) resumes and has been racing well in stronger than this. He's won 2/4 fresh and brings a Belmont trial win. Needs a good ride but is a live hope. SECRET STONES (7) missed a nose first-up over 1100m, making further improvement. Has a low gate again, and the in-form Galati replaced the apprentice. He's placed 2/3 second up, and fitter, he's sure to give a big sight. WHIPLASH (9) resumes and has switched from a top Victorian stable. He led and won a Sale Maiden two back, and that's good form. Has the inside barrier, and the betting will tell the story with him.
